(103, 1, '2015-11-09 06:18:59', '2015-11-09 06:18:59', '<div class="main aboutUs">\r\n<div class="aboutUsSection one">\r\n<div class="harvardOverlay">\r\n<div class="widthWrapper">\r\n<h2 class="blueText">In 2012 we met at Harvard and recognized our shared dedication to helping families of children with disabilities gain better access to services and supports. We knew disability information was available, but that much of it was too general or inaccessible for families who needed it. To solve this problem, we began collaborating on technology solutions that could empower families with access to essential information, tailored to their individual situations. In 2013, we launched Exceptional Lives.</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="aboutUsSection two">\r\n<div class="widthWrapper">\r\n<h1 class="theTeam">The Team</h1>\r\n<div class="flexWrapper">\r\n<div class="bio">\r\n\r\n<img src="/wp-content/themes/exceptional-lives/images/jay-w-obrien.png" alt="Jay O''Brien" />\r\n<h1 class="name">Jay O''Brien</h1>\r\n<p class="position">Co-founder and Executive Director</p>\r\n<p class="bioWriteup">Jay O’Brien has worked in the disability field for 12 years, following positions in the US Senate in Washington andhigh-tech marketing communications in Boston. His experience includes nine years as a field office director and corporate fundraiser for Special Olympics Massachusetts. Jay received an MPA from The Harvard Kennedy School where he was a Harvard Alumni Public Service Fellow. He has BA from Holy Cross College.</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="bio">\r\n\r\n<img src="/wp-content/themes/exceptional-lives/images/anne-punzak-marcus.png" alt="Anne Punzak Marcus" />\r\n<h1 class="name">Anne Punzak Marcus</h1>\r\n<p class="position">Co-founder and Board Chair</p>\r\n<p class="bioWriteup">Anne Punzak Marcus has over ten years of experience working with organizations focused on brain disorders, education, and health. She is a co-founder of the Autism Consortium, a Boston-based organization that brings together clinicians, researchers, and families to expedite autism research. Previously, Anne worked at Fidelity Investments as a portfolio manager and Research Director. Anne was a 2012 and 2013 Harvard Advanced Leadership Fellow. She earned her MBA from The Wharton School after receiving her BS from Boston College.</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="bio">\r\n\r\n<img src="/wp-content/themes/exceptional-lives/images/chris-spence.png" alt="Chris Spence" />\r\n<h1 class="name">Christopher Spence</h1>\r\n<p class="position">Chief Technology Officer</p>\r\n<p class="bioWriteup">Chris Spence oversees the development of Exceptional Lives’ interactive product suite. He spent several years as a high school science teacher before combining his love of education with technology and moving into. Chris earned an M.Ed. in Technology, Innovation &amp; Education from the Harvard School of Education and has a B. S. from Williams College.</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="bio">\r\n\r\n<img src="/wp-content/themes/exceptional-lives/images/ryan-eckenrode.png" alt="Ryan Eckenrode" />\r\n<h1 class="name">Ryan Eckendrode</h1>\r\n<p class="position">Vice President, Marketing and Partnerships</p>\r\n<p class="bioWriteup">Ryan Eckenrode oversees Exceptional Lives’ marketing and community partnerships. Previously, Ryan worked in the finance, insurance and technology industries, helping organizations get the most out of their sales, marketing, and customer success efforts through technology and business development initiatives. Ryan earned his BA from Point Park University and a BRM from Carnegie Mellon University.</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="bio">\r\n\r\n<img src="/wp-content/themes/exceptional-lives/images/tom-wilhelm.png" alt="Tom Wilhelm" />\r\n<h1 class="name">Tom Wilhelm</h1>\r\n<p class="position">Product/Project Manager</p>\r\n<p class="bioWriteup">Tom has spent a decade driving process improvement in the ever-evolving educational technology space. He earned a BA from Wesleyan University. Tom is also a Scrum Alliance Certified Scrum Product Owner.</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="bio">\r\n\r\n<img src="/wp-content/themes/exceptional-lives/images/tj-loughlin.png" alt="TJ Loughlin" />\r\n<h1 class="name">TJ Loughlin</h1>\r\n<p class="position">Software Engineer</p>\r\n<p class="bioWriteup">TJ Loughlin helps engineer the software that empowers Exceptional Lives. TJ came to Exceptional Lives from the video gaming industry, where he learned how to build simple,engaging products. TJ earned his BS in Interactive Media and Game Development from the Worcester Polytechnic Institute.</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="aboutUsSection three">\r\n<div id="widthWrapper">\r\n<h1 class="boardOfDirectors blueText">Board of Directors</h1>\r\n<div class="flexWrapper">\r\n<div class="directorBio">\r\n<h1>Charles Johnson, JD</h1>\r\nMr. Johnson is a apartner at the Boston law firm Choate Hall &amp; Stewart, LLC where he practices business law and is a member of the firm''s executive committee. He has an adult son with Down syndrome and serves on the board of directors of Special Olympics Massachusetts.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="directorBio">\r\n<h1>Christine Letts, MBA</h1>\r\nMs. Letts is the Rita E. Hauser Senior Lecturer in the Practice of Philanthropy and Nonprofit Leadership at Harvard Kennedy School (HKS). She has extensive experience in private, nonprofit and public management. She was the founding executive director of HKS''s Hauser Center for Nonprofit Organizations (now the Hauser Institute for Civil Society at the Center for Public Leadership). She is the author of High Performance Nonprofit Organizations and Social Entrepreneurship and Societal Transformation.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="directorBio">\r\n<h1>Carol Raphael, MPA</h1>\r\nMs. Raphael is board chair of the AARP. She is former President and CEO of the Visiting Nurse Service of New York, the largest nonprofit home health agency in the US. She also currently chairs the New York eHealth Collaborative, a public-private partnership working to advance the adoption of health information technology. She is a member of numerous advisory boards including the Harvard School of Public Health''s Health Policy Management Executive Council.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="footerBlue">\r\n<div id="widthWrapper" class="flex fullHeight">\r\n<div class="left">\r\n<h2>Follow us on social media</h2>\r\n<div class="socialIconsWrap"><a href="https://www.facebook.com/exceptional.lives" target="_blank"><i class="facebookIcon"></i></a><a href="https://twitter.com/xceptionallives" target="_blank"><i class="twitterIcon"></i></a><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/company/10226036" target="_blank"><i class="linkedinIcon"></i></a><a href="#"><i class="instagramIcon"></i></a></div>\r\n<p class="blueCopyright">© Copyright 2015 Exceptional Lives. All Rights Reserved.</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="right">\r\n<h2>Subscribe to our blog for updates:</h2>\r\n[sola_nl_sign_up]\r\nWe do not spam. Read our <a href="#">privacy policy</a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'About Us', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '6-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-11-09 06:18:59', '2015-11-09 06:18:59', '', 6, 'http://localhost:8888/2015/11/09/6-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(104, 1, '2015-11-09 06:19:19', '2015-11-09 06:19:19', '<div class="main ourVision"><section class="secOne bgImage">\r\n<div class="overlay">\r\n<div id="widthWrapper">\r\n<div class="bannerConstrain">\r\n<p class="">Our Vision:<br class="" />Everyone with a developmental disability, delay or mental health disorder has the right to an exceptional life.</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</section><section class="secTwo">\r\n<div id="widthWrapper" class="flex">\r\n<div class="left">\r\n<h3 class="blueText">Benefits of an Exceptional Lives Process Guide™:</h3>\r\n<ul class="orangeText">\r\n	<li>Give you actionable information.</li>\r\n	<li>Customizes it to your unique situation.</li>\r\n	<li>Walks you through it step by step.</li>\r\n	<li>Reduces your stress and anxiety.</li>\r\n	<li>Makes you fell better prepared.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="right">\r\n<h3 class="blueText">What Parents Say:</h3>\r\n<p class="quote"><img src="/wp-content/themes/exceptional-lives/images/quotation.jpg" alt="" />The Process Guide gives you the peace of mind that you''re thinking of, covering and managing all these things.</p>\r\n<p class="quote"><img src="/wp-content/themes/exceptional-lives/images/quotation.jpg" alt="" />I now feel confident that we''ll be able to easily reach the information we need, without having to spend 10 more years sorting through what is important for other families but not for us.</p>\r\n<p class="quote"><img src="/wp-content/themes/exceptional-lives/images/quotation.jpg" alt="" />GREAT IDEA.</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</section><section class="secThree bgImage">\r\n<div class="overlay">\r\n<div id="widthWrapper">\r\n<div class="overlay">\r\n<div class="bannerConstrain">\r\n\r\nEach Exceptional Lives Process Guide™ is developed with the help of subject matter experts. The Process Guides we develop utilize the latest research and best practices.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</section></div>\r\n<div class="footerBlue">\r\n<div id="widthWrapper" class="flex fullHeight">\r\n<div class="left">\r\n<h2>Follow us on social media</h2>\r\n<div class="socialIconsWrap"><a href="https://www.facebook.com/exceptional.lives" target="_blank"><i class="facebookIcon"></i></a><a href="https://twitter.com/xceptionallives" target="_blank"><i class="twitterIcon"></i></a><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/company/10226036" target="_blank"><i class="linkedinIcon"></i></a><a href="#"><i class="instagramIcon"></i></a></div>\r\n<p class="blueCopyright">&copy; Copyright 2015 Exceptional Lives. All Rights Reserved.</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="right">\r\n<h2>Subscribe to our blog for updates:</h2>\r\n[sola_nl_sign_up]\r\nWe do not spam. Read our <a href="#">privacy policy</a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'Our Vision', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '8-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-11-09 06:19:19', '2015-11-09 06:19:19', '', 8, 'http://localhost:8888/2015/11/09/8-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
