(170, 1, '2015-11-10 09:57:11', '2015-11-10 09:57:11', '<div class="main aboutUs-ourExperts">\r\n<div class="aboutUs-ourExpertsSection one">\r\n<div class="harvardOverlay">\r\n<div id="widthWrapper">\r\n<h2 class="blueText">Each Exceptional Lives Process Guide™ is developed with the help of subject matter experts. The Process Guides we develop utilize the latest research and best practices.</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="aboutUs-ourExpertsSection two extraBottom">\r\n<div id="widthWrapper">\r\n<h1 class="theTeam">Our Experts</h1>\r\n<div class="flexWrapper">\r\n<div class="bio">\r\n<img src="/wp-content/themes/exceptional-lives/images/theresa-varnet.png">\r\n<h1 class="name">Theresa M Varnet</h1>\r\n<p class="position">JD, MSW</p>\r\n<p class="bioWriteup">Theresa is a special needs attorney with Fletcher Tilton PC. She has been an advocate for persons with disabilities for more than 40 years. In addition to being a lawyer, she is a certified teacher, licensed social worker, and the parent of a disabled adult daughter. She has served as social services director in a residential school for children with multiple disabilities, coordinator for a special education cooperative, and as a citizen advocacy/disability rights coordinator. She has degrees from the University of Massachusetts, University of Connecticut, and DePaul University.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="bio">\r\n<img src="/wp-content/themes/exceptional-lives/images/deirdre-phillips.png">\r\n<h1 class="name">Deirdre B. Phillips</h1>\r\n<p class="position">MA</p>\r\n<p class="bioWriteup">As Executive Director of the Autism Consortium, Deirdre has led the effort to bring together Boston scientists and clinicians to increase understanding and improve treatments for autism. More than 10,000 families have benefited from the Consortium’s resources, and many have become involved in autism research. She has been active in the autism community for more than 25 years, advocating for insurance coverage for testing and treatment, better training for autism professionals, and increased employment opportunities for individuals with disabilities. Deirdre was recently appointed by Governor Charles Baker to serve as a member of the Massachusetts Autism Commission. She is a graduate of Wheaton College.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="bio">\r\n<img src="/wp-content/themes/exceptional-lives/images/liz-muller.png">\r\n<h1 class="name">Elizabeth Muller</h1>\r\n<p class="position">EdM, MA, LMHC</p>\r\n<p class="bioWriteup">A licensed mental health counselor, Elizabeth has helped adolescents, families, and adults reach their highest potential for more than 20 years. Her expertise includes working with adolescents and adults who experience depression, anxiety, relationships, self-injurious behaviors, identity development, grief, academic counseling, and life transitions. Her therapeutic approach is based on the individual client’s goals and present life concerns. Elizabeth earned degrees from Harvard Graduate School of Education and Lesley University.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="bio">\r\n<img src="/wp-content/themes/exceptional-lives/images/lester-hartman.png">\r\n<h1 class="name">Lester K Hartman</h1>\r\n<p class="position">MD, MPH</p>\r\n<p class="bioWriteup">Dr. Hartman has been a member of Westwood-Mansfield Pediatric Associates since 1986. His primary focus is empowering parents and caregivers to manage their children’s health and family’s wellbeing. He has a special interest in children with exceptional needs, helping coordinate care-related issues in school and at home. His affiliations include Boston Children’s Hospital, where he served on the board of the Pediatric Physicians Organization at Children’s (PPOC) for 16 years. Lester holds degrees from Harvard School of Public Health and Louisiana State University.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="footerBlue borderTop">\r\n<div class="flex fullHeight" id="widthWrapper">\r\n<div class="left">\r\n<h2>Follow us on social media</h2>\r\n<div class="socialIconsWrap"><ul>\r\n<li><a href="https://www.facebook.com/exceptional.lives" target="_blank"><i class="facebookIcon"></i></a></li>\r\n<li><a href="https://twitter.com/xceptionallives" target="_blank"><i class="twitterIcon"></i></a></li>\r\n<li><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/company/10226036" target="_blank"><i class="linkedinIcon"></i></a></li>\r\n<li><a href="https://instagram.com/exceptional.lives/"><i class="instagramIcon"></i></a></li>\r\n</ul></div>\r\n<p class="blueCopyright">&copy; Copyright Exceptional Lives. All Rights Reserved.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="right"><h2>Subscribe to our blog for updates:</h2>[sola_nl_sign_up]<p class="clear"></p><p>We do not spam. Read our <a href="http://exceptionallives.org/TermsOfService">privacy policy</a></p></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'Our Experts', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '15-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-11-10 09:57:11', '2015-11-10 09:57:11', '', 15, 'http://localhost:8888/2015/11/10/15-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(171, 1, '2015-11-10 09:59:53', '2015-11-10 09:59:53', '<div class="main aboutUs">\r\n<div class="aboutUsSection one">\r\n<div class="harvardOverlay">\r\n<div id="widthWrapper">\r\n<h2 class="blueText">In 2012 we met at Harvard and recognized our shared dedication to helping families of children with disabilities gain better access to services and supports. We knew disability information was available, but that much of it was too general or inaccessible for families who needed it. To solve this problem, we began collaborating on technology solutions that could empower families with access to essential information, tailored to their individual situations. In 2013, we launched Exceptional Lives.</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="aboutUsSection two">\r\n<div id="widthWrapper">\r\n<h1 class="theTeam">The Team</h1>\r\n<div class="flexWrapper">\r\n<div class="bio">\r\n<img alt="Jay O''Brien" src="/wp-content/themes/exceptional-lives/images/jay-w-obrien.png">\r\n<h1 class="name">Jay O''Brien</h1>\r\n<p class="position">Co-founder and Executive Director</p>\r\n<p class="bioWriteup">Jay O’Brien has worked in the disability field for 12 years, following positions in the US Senate in Washington and high-tech marketing communications in Boston. His experience includes nine years as a field office director and corporate fundraiser for Special Olympics Massachusetts. Jay received an MPA from The Harvard Kennedy School where he was a Harvard Alumni Public Service Fellow. He has BA from Holy Cross College.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="bio">\r\n<img alt="Anne Punzak Marcus" src="/wp-content/themes/exceptional-lives/images/anne-punzak-marcus.png">\r\n<h1 class="name">Anne Punzak Marcus</h1>\r\n<p class="position">Co-founder and Board Chair</p>\r\n<p class="bioWriteup">Anne Punzak Marcus has over ten years of experience working with organizations focused on brain disorders, education, and health. She is a co-founder of the Investments as a portfolio manager and Research Director. Anne was a 2012 and 2013 Harvard Advanced Leadership Fellow. She earned her MBA from The Wharton School after receiving her BS from Boston College.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="bio">\r\n<img alt="Chris Spence" src="/wp-content/themes/exceptional-lives/images/chris-spence.png">\r\n<h1 class="name">Christopher Spence</h1>\r\n<p class="position">Chief Technology Officer</p>\r\n<p class="bioWriteup">Chris Spence oversees the development of Exceptional Lives’ interactive product suite. He spent several years as a high school science teacher before combining his love of education with technology and moving into. Chris earned an M.Ed. in Technology, Innovation &amp; Education from the Harvard School of Education and has a B.S. from Williams College.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="bio">\r\n<img alt="Ryan Eckenrode" src="/wp-content/themes/exceptional-lives/images/ryan-eckenrode.png">\r\n<h1 class="name">Ryan Eckendrode</h1>\r\n<p class="position">Vice President, Marketing and Partnerships</p>\r\n<p class="bioWriteup">Ryan Eckenrode oversees Exceptional Lives’ marketing and community partnerships. Previously, Ryan worked in the finance, insurance and technology industries, helping organizations get the most out of their sales, marketing, and customer success efforts through technology and business development initiatives. Ryan earned his BA from Point Park University and a BRM from Carnegie Mellon University.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="bio">\r\n<img alt="Tom Wilhelm" src="/wp-content/themes/exceptional-lives/images/tom-wilhelm.png">\r\n<h1 class="name">Tom Wilhelm</h1>\r\n<p class="position">Product/Project Manager</p>\r\n<p class="bioWriteup">Tom has spent a decade driving process improvement in the ever-evolving educational technology space. He earned a BA from Wesleyan University. Tom is also a Scrum Alliance Certified Scrum Product Owner.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="bio">\r\n<img alt="TJ Loughlin" src="/wp-content/themes/exceptional-lives/images/tj-loughlin.png">\r\n<h1 class="name">TJ Loughlin</h1>\r\n<p class="position">Software Engineer</p>\r\n<p class="bioWriteup">TJ Loughlin helps engineer the software that empowers Exceptional Lives. TJ came to Exceptional Lives from the video gaming industry, where he learned how to build simple,engaging products. TJ earned his BS in Interactive Media and Game Development from the Worcester Polytechnic Institute.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="aboutUsSection three">\r\n<div id="widthWrapper">\r\n<h1 class="boardOfDirectors blueText">Board of Directors</h1>\r\n<div class="flexWrapper">\r\n<div class="directorBio">\r\n<h1>Charles Johnson, JD</h1>\r\n<p>Mr. Johnson is a a partner at the Boston law firm Choate Hall &amp; Stewart, LLC where he practices business law and is a member of the firm''s executive committee. He has an adult son with Down syndrome and serves on the board of directors of Special Olympics Massachusetts.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="directorBio">\r\n<h1>Christine Letts, MBA</h1>\r\n<p>Ms. Letts is the Rita E. Hauser Senior Lecturer in the Practice of Philanthropy and Nonprofit Leadership at Harvard Kennedy School (HKS). She has extensive experience in private, nonprofit and public management. She was the founding executive director of HKS''s Hauser Center for Nonprofit Organizations (now the Hauser Institute for Civil Society at the Center for Public Leadership). She is the author of High Performance Nonprofit Organizations and Social Entrepreneurship and Societal Transformation.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="directorBio">\r\n<h1>Carol Raphael, MPA</h1>\r\n<p>Ms. Raphael is board chair of the AARP. She is former President and CEO of the Visiting Nurse Service of New York, the largest nonprofit home health agency in the US. She also currently chairs the New York eHealth Collaborative, a public-private partnership working to advance the adoption of health information technology. She is a member of numerous advisory boards including the Harvard School of Public Health''s Health Policy Management Executive Council.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="footerBlue">\r\n<div class="flex fullHeight" id="widthWrapper">\r\n<div class="left">\r\n<h2>Follow us on social media</h2>\r\n<div class="socialIconsWrap"><ul>\r\n<li><a href="https://www.facebook.com/exceptional.lives" target="_blank"><i class="facebookIcon"></i></a></li>\r\n<li><a href="https://twitter.com/xceptionallives" target="_blank"><i class="twitterIcon"></i></a></li>\r\n<li><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/company/10226036" target="_blank"><i class="linkedinIcon"></i></a></li>\r\n<li><a href="https://instagram.com/exceptional.lives/"><i class="instagramIcon"></i></a></li>\r\n</ul></div>\r\n<p class="blueCopyright">&copy; Copyright Exceptional Lives. All Rights Reserved.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="right"><h2>Subscribe to our blog for updates:</h2>[sola_nl_sign_up]<p class="clear"></p><p>We do not spam. Read our <a href="http://exceptionallives.org/TermsOfService">privacy policy</a></p></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'About Us', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '6-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-11-10 09:59:53', '2015-11-10 09:59:53', '', 6, 'http://localhost:8888/2015/11/10/6-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(172, 1, '2015-11-10 10:00:53', '2015-11-10 10:00:53', '<div class="main ourVision">\r\n<section class="secOne bgImage">\r\n<div class="overlay">\r\n<div id="widthWrapper">\r\n<div class="bannerConstrain">\r\n<p>Our Vision:<br/>Everyone with a developmental disability, delay or mental health disorder has the right to an exceptional life.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</section>\r\n<section class="secTwo">\r\n<div class="flex" id="widthWrapper">\r\n<div class="left">\r\n<h3 class="blueText">Benefits of an Exceptional Lives Process Guide™:</h3>\r\n<ul class="orangeText">\r\n<li>Give you actionable information.</li>\r\n<li>Customizes it to your unique situation.</li>\r\n<li>Walks you through it step by step.</li>\r\n<li>Reduces your stress and anxiety.</li>\r\n<li>Makes you fell better prepared.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="right">\r\n<h3 class="blueText">What Parents Say:</h3>\r\n<p class="quote"><img alt="" src="/wp-content/themes/exceptional-lives/images/quotation.jpg">The Process Guide gives you the peace of mind that you''re thinking of, covering and\r\nmanaging all these things.</p>\r\n<p class="quote"><img alt="" src="/wp-content/themes/exceptional-lives/images/quotation.jpg">I now feel confident that we''ll be able to easily reach the information we need, without\r\nhaving to spend 10 more years sorting through what is important for other families but not for us.</p>\r\n<p class="quote"><img alt="" src="/wp-content/themes/exceptional-lives/images/quotation.jpg">GREAT IDEA.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</section>\r\n<section class="secThree bgImage">\r\n<div class="overlay">\r\n<div id="widthWrapper">\r\n<div class="overlay">\r\n<div class="bannerConstrain">\r\n<p>Each Exceptional Lives Process Guide™ is developed with the help of subject matter experts. The Process Guides we develop utilize the latest research and best practices.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</section>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="footerBlue">\r\n<div class="flex fullHeight" id="widthWrapper">\r\n<div class="left">\r\n<h2>Follow us on social media</h2>\r\n<div class="socialIconsWrap"><ul>\r\n<li><a href="https://www.facebook.com/exceptional.lives" target="_blank"><i class="facebookIcon"></i></a></li>\r\n<li><a href="https://twitter.com/xceptionallives" target="_blank"><i class="twitterIcon"></i></a></li>\r\n<li><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/company/10226036" target="_blank"><i class="linkedinIcon"></i></a></li>\r\n<li><a href="https://instagram.com/exceptional.lives/"><i class="instagramIcon"></i></a></li>\r\n</ul></div>\r\n<p class="blueCopyright">&copy; Copyright Exceptional Lives. All Rights Reserved.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="right"><h2>Subscribe to our blog for updates:</h2>[sola_nl_sign_up]<p class="clear"></p><p>We do not spam. Read our <a href="http://exceptionallives.org/TermsOfService">privacy policy</a></p></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'Our Vision', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '8-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-11-10 10:00:53', '2015-11-10 10:00:53', '', 8, 'http://localhost:8888/2015/11/10/8-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(173, 1, '2015-11-10 10:01:36', '2015-11-10 10:01:36', '<div class="main homePage">\r\n<section class="secOne">\r\n<div id="widthWrapper">\r\n<div class="central">\r\n<h1>Individualized How-to Guides to help exceptional family members thrive</h1><img alt="Paula" class="homeLargeImage mariaImage" src="/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/paula.png" />\r\n<h1 class="meetMaria">Meet Paula</h1>\r\n<h2>Paula has a 13-year-old with special needs. Worrying about his future keeps her up at night. Information online is overwhelming, unreliable and generic. Expert help is too expensive.</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n<aside>\r\n<h3>Our Free Guides</h3>\r\n<p>Click a button below to check out an Exceptional Lives Guide! Create your own account (takes 15 seconds) and explore all our Guides. It''s that easy.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<a class="button buttonStackSpacing firstBut" href="https://navitomeapp.com/?pid=303">Create an effective IEP</a>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<a class="button buttonStackSpacing" href="https://navitomeapp.com/?pid=268">Optimize health insurance</a>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<a class="button buttonStackSpacing" href="https://navitomeapp.com/?pid=357">Apply for SSI</a>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<a class="button buttonStackSpacing" href="https://navitomeapp.com/?pid=184">Navigate guardianship</a>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class="donate">Donate</h3>\r\n<p>Each Exceptional Lives Guide takes many hours to research, publish and update. Keep them free (and ad-free) for everyone by making a donation today.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<a class="button buttonStackSpacing firstBut" href="https://www.givingcommon.org/profile/1142565/exceptional-lives-inc/#8">Donate</a>\r\n</p>\r\n<img alt="Guidestar Logo" class="guidestarSilver" src="/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/guidestarSilver.png" />\r\n</aside>\r\n</div>\r\n</section>\r\n<section class="secTwo">\r\n<div id="widthWrapper">\r\n<img alt="Laptop Screenshot" class="homeLargeImage laptop" src="/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/laptop.png" />\r\n<h2>When she visits the Exceptional Lives website, she finds free, easy-to-understand online guides for families of children and adults with disabilities in Massachusetts.</h2>\r\n<h1>Each guide takes as little as 15 minutes to walk through!</h1>\r\n</div>\r\n</section>\r\n<section class="secThree">\r\n<div id="widthWrapper">\r\n<img alt="Guides Screenshot 1" class="squareImg" src="/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/screenshot1.png" />\r\n<h2>As Paula moves through a Guide, she answers questions. The software behind the Guides uses these answers to customize the information she sees.</h2><img alt="Guides Screenshot 2" class="squareImg" src="/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/screenshot2.png" />\r\n<h2>Each Guide gives her clear next steps that empower her to take action and achieve goals.</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n</section>\r\n<section class="secFour">\r\n<div id="widthWrapper">\r\n<img alt="Paula 2" class="homeLargeImage cartoon" src="/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/paula2.png" />\r\n<h2>By using Exceptional Lives Guides, Paula has more knowledge and confidence about how to access the necessary supports and services that will help her son thrive.</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n</section>\r\n<section class="secFive">\r\n<div id="widthWrapper">\r\n<div class="central">\r\n<h1>Ready to get started?</h1>\r\n<h2>Click a button below to check out an Exceptional Lives Guide! Create your own account (takes 15 seconds), and explore all our Guides. It''s that easy.</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<a class="button buttonStackSpacing firstBut" href="https://navitomeapp.com/?pid=303">Create an effective IEP</a>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<a class="button buttonStackSpacing" href="https://navitomeapp.com/?pid=268">Optimize health insurance</a>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<a class="button buttonStackSpacing" href="https://navitomeapp.com/?pid=357">Apply for SSI</a>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<a class="button buttonStackSpacing" href="https://navitomeapp.com/?pid=184">Navigate guardianship</a>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<aside>\r\n<h3>Subscribe to our blog:</h3>\r\n[sola_nl_sign